On Tue, 16 Sep 2008, Marlboro63@... wrote:

&gt; Hi Zack,
&gt;
&gt; Read my review of the Ovilus 1.  The common mistake is that everyone  turns
&gt; it on and expects to get immediate results.  Well all that comes out  is random
&gt; names and what some people may term &quot;garbage&quot; at that time.  You  have to let
&gt; the spirits around you learn how to communicate thru the box  and this can
&gt; take a good 30 to 60 minutes.  At that time all the randomness  will have died
&gt; down and you can now start to communicate thru the Ovilus  1.  If this step is
&gt; overlooked then you just sit there staring at this unit  thinking you just
&gt; pissed away $200.00.  And that is not the case.  It  takes time for the spirits
&gt; to learn how to communicate regardless of what device  is used.  Now if you use
&gt; this device in the same location over and over  again you only have to do it
&gt; once.  When I first got mine it was spewing  out all kind of random garbage
&gt; that made sense.  But once I did this the  communication flowed fluently.  It
&gt; even gave me the name of the little girl  who&#39;s spirit inhabits our house and
&gt; when I called her name after hearing it this  little girl came and stood in the
&gt; hallway looking at me in amazement.  The  best was when my cat jumped up by me
&gt; and the Ovilus 1 and wanted attention the  Ovilus 1 said &quot;good cat&quot;.  Then
&gt; when my dog ran into the room and wanted my  attention over the cat the unit
&gt; said &quot;bad dog&quot;, LOL.  So it does work and  ask around to people who have them
&gt; about their experiences.
&gt;
&gt; Jeff
